label.value: Experimental Organism Islet Cell Adenoma Neoplasm

value.value: A benign neoplasm arising from the islet cells of the pancreas.
A malignant epithelial neoplasm of the anterior pituitary gland in which the neoplastic cells stain positive with acidic dyes.
A malignant neoplasm of large lymphocytes, which resemble histiocytes.
A malignant neoplasm composed of a mixed lymphocyte population.
An antiquated term referring to a malignant lymphoma that is diffused and composed of small and large lymphocytes.

label.value: Experimental Organism Benign Stromal Tumor Neoplasm

value.value: A benign neoplasm composed of mesenchymal stromal cells.
A benign germ-cell neoplasm derived from pluripotent cells and consisting of components from one or more of the three germ-cell layers.
A benign neoplasm of the thymus, originating from epithelial thymus cells.

value.value: The total body clearance for extravascular administration for dose interval, where F is the fraction of dose absorbed.

value.value: The total body clearance for intravascular administration for dose interval.

After delivery of neonate, placental retention that requires clinical intervention such as manual extraction, curettage or uterotonic medications.

The stimulation of uterine contractions using pharmacologic methods or artificial rupture of membranes (AROM) to increase their frequency and/or strength following the onset of spontaneous labor or contractions following spontaneous rupture of membranes. Does not apply if induction of labor is performed. (reVITALize)
A procedure during labor in which the occiput is manually rotated from posterior to anterior.
The birth of a cephalically presenting fetus without operative instrumentation or assistance.
The birth of a breech-presenting fetus without operative instrumentation or assistance.
The delivery of a breech-presenting fetus with that is manually pulled through the birth canal.

label.value: Trial of Birth Labor after Cesarean

value.value: Trial of labor in a woman with a previous cesarean delivery regardless of ultimate route of delivery.
The first surgical delivery of one or more intrauterine fetuses though an abdominal incision in a woman without prior cesarean delivery.
A regimen consisting of carboplatin, gemcitabine, and paclitaxel that may be used in the treatment of advanced ovarian carcinoma and non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC).
The surgical delivery of one or more intrauterine fetuses though an abdominal incision in a woman who has had prior cesarean delivery(ies).
A cesarean delivery scheduled at a patient's request or provider preference without medical or obstetric indications.
A cesarean delivery that is performed for specific, medical or obstetric indications, which may be scheduled or unscheduled.
Extraction of a fetus through the cervix using destructive surgical techniques.
A test that measures the verbal fluency of an individual. This tool measures both semantic fluency and phonetic fluency.
The type of electrode used on the subject during electrical stimulation of the body or organ.
A finding referring to a medical device that has been removed from the body, usually during a surgical procedure.

An electrocardiographic recording in which the isoelectric line in one or more leads is vertically displaced resulting in low frequency upward and downward movements of the signal with varying amplitudes. (CDISC)
An electrocardiographic recording with intermittent mid to high frequency artifact in one or more leads due to muscular tremor or movement rather than cardiac activity. (CDISC)

label.value: Alternating Current Noise by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording showing power line interference with the electrocardiographic signal. The artifact amplitude modulation has the same frequency as the AC power system present (usually 50 Hz or 60 Hz). (CDISC)

label.value: Interchanged Limb Electrodes by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which two or more of the limb electrodes are switched resulting in improper representation of the affected leads. (CDISC)

label.value: Disconnected Limb Electrodes by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which one or more of the limb electrodes are disconnected resulting in missing waveforms (often flat lines) of the respective leads. (CDISC)
